
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  MISSION: CONFIGURATION REPAIR                                            ║
║  SKILL: sed (stream editor)                                               ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

OBJECTIVE:
The reactor configuration file has been corrupted. Several values have
been changed to "CORRUPTED" and need to be restored to their correct
settings.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASK: Restore the Configuration File
────────────────────────────────────
The file 'reactor.cfg' contains the reactor configuration.
Some values show "CORRUPTED" instead of their proper values.

Reference the 'reactor.cfg.reference' file to see what the
correct values should be.

Create a fixed version of the config by using sed to replace
the corrupted values. Save it as 'reactor_fixed.cfg'.

When ready, run:
    ./verify

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

USEFUL COMMANDS:
    cat reactor.cfg                        View corrupted config
    cat reactor.cfg.reference              View correct values
    diff reactor.cfg reactor.cfg.reference Compare files

    sed 's/CORRUPTED/value/' file          Replace CORRUPTED
    sed 's/old/new/g' file > newfile       Save to new file

EXAMPLE (replace one specific line):
    If line says: power_output=CORRUPTED
    And should be: power_output=85

    sed 's/power_output=CORRUPTED/power_output=85/' reactor.cfg

You may need multiple sed commands or chain them:
    sed 's/X/Y/' file | sed 's/A/B/' > output

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

